From 40958de7971bddc3e2631935a6c01c9d97e88b5b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Max Furman <taygoth@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 1 Jun 2026 00:19:42 +0500
Subject: [PATCH 1/9] Input: touchscreen/stm/ftm5: throttle zero-pressure
 warning
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The pointer event handler logs an error every time the firmware reports
pressure 0 with the contact still present. On firmware variants that
always report pressure 0 (observed on Mi 8 / dipper with Xiaomi's
`st_fts_e1.ftb`), this fires once per CSI event — tens of `pr_err`
lines per touch tap and hundreds per swipe. The driver already clamps
the value to 1 to keep the touch alive, so the only effect is dmesg
flooding.

Replace `pr_err()` with `pr_warn_once()` so the diagnostic still
surfaces firmware quirks on first occurrence but does not drown the log
on continued operation. Behaviour on firmware that does report real
pressure is unchanged (the warning never triggers).

Signed-off-by: Max Furman <taygoth@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/input/touchscreen/stm/fts.c | 13 +++++++------
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/input/touchscreen/stm/fts.c b/drivers/input/touchscreen/stm/fts.c
index ed33835e8..8e35cf7a4 100644
--- a/drivers/input/touchscreen/stm/fts.c
+++ b/drivers/input/touchscreen/stm/fts.c
@@ -2481,13 +2481,14 @@ static bool fts_enter_pointer_event_handler(struct fts_ts_info *info, unsigned
 	y = ((int)event[4] << 4) | ((event[3] & 0xF0) >> 4);
 	z = (int)event[5];
 	if (z <= 0) {
-		/* Should not happen, because zero pressure implies contact has
-		 * left, so this function should not be invoked. For safety, to
-		 * prevent this touch from being dropped, set to smallest
-		 * pressure value instead
+		/* Some firmware variants (observed: Mi 8/dipper
+		 * st_fts_e1.ftb) always report pressure 0 on every event.
+		 * Clamp to smallest non-zero pressure so the touch is not
+		 * dropped, and warn once so the firmware quirk stays visible
+		 * without flooding dmesg.
 		 */
-		pr_err("%s: Pressure is %i, but pointer is not leaving\n",
-		       __func__, z);
+		pr_warn_once("%s: firmware reports zero pressure, clamping to 1\n",
+			     __func__);
 		z = 1; /* smallest non-zero pressure value */
 	}
 	major = (int)(((event[0] & 0x0C) << 2) | ((event[6] & 0xF0) >> 4));
-- 
